definition: A unique numeric identifier assigned to the originating source data's program.
Unique global identifier assigned to the location where the event occurred.
noteAndConventions: generated when the datasets are combined into a single dataset

definition: The verbatim location ID from the originating source dataset assigned by the monitoring program.
The geographic latitude (WGS84) of the geographic center of a location.
noteAndConventions: latitude and longitudes the coordinate reference system is World Geodetic System 1984 (WGS84), not projected.

definition: The geographic longitude (WGS84) of the geographic center of a location.
noteAndConventions: latitude and longitudes the coordinate reference system is World Geodetic System 1984 (WGS84), not projected.

definition: The location along the reach where geographic coordinates were obtained.
The type of site selection used according to the program.
NAdefinition: Site selection not known or reported by the program.

definition: The name of the water body in which the location occurs.
NAdefinition: Water body name not reported in the original dataset.
